What is a class?
- Non-primitive data type (like string)
- classes divided into two:
    -> built-in classes:                                    ->custom classes:
       already defined in the Java standard library           created by developers based on needs
       also known as pre-defined/standard classes
        ->string, scanner, math

- classes specify state & behavior of objects
- class is a blueprint (template) of whichever object it is created from
- when creating classes separated into
    -> field (state): set of values stored in an object
    -> Method (behaviour):set of action objects can perform

What does Object mean:
- entity that has state and behaviour of class
- instance of class (also an name for it)

   -> Field is a set of values stored in an object
   -> Method is a set of action an object can perform

   - once class is created , by adding fields and methods, you can create multiple objects from it
   - instances of class can be  created  if you want to create methods and classes
        you need to create an object, instances of classes need to be created

   EXAMPLE:
   public class Teacher {                   => Class Header

   public String name;
   public int age;
   public String email;                     => Fields
   public String branch;
   public boolean isManager;

   public void teachSubject(){
    sout("teaching...");
    }
   public void practicingSubject(){
    sout("practicing subject...");
    }
   public void teachSubject(){              => Methods
    sout("teaching...");
    }
   public void solveQuestions(){
    sout("solving questions...");
    }
    public void give homework(){
    sout("giving homework...");
    }
