   Instance Variables And Methods

   - fields and methods that belong to any instances of a class are called
     instance variables and instance methods
     -> Instance Variables:
        - declared inside the class and outside any method/ block
        - belong to the object , and each object has its own memory
        - each object has a separate copy of the instance variable

     -> Instance Methods:
        (methods learned so far are called static methods)
        - do not have static keyword
        - belong to the object
        - each object has a separate copy of the instance methods
        - by making methods instance , I will be able to call those methods separately from each object
          then action will be performed that specific object
          -> which object gets to be run first depends on from which object you're calling this method from
