Difference between class and objects:

- Class: where all objects come from
  - template for creating objects
  - states and behaviours created there are what objects will have
  - every single object you are creating from the class are known instances of that class


  Class                                             Object
  - blueprint from which objects is created         - is an instance of class
  - is a template(conceptual)                       - is real
  - no memory is allocated                          - each object occupies own space in memory
  - can exist without any objects                   - cannot exist without a class
  - no values associated with the field             - every object has own value associated with the field
